column5: I just used this place for my printer and the products are good.  http://www.inkjetsuperstore.ca/

I just bought 4 different cartridges for my Epsom Stylus NX130...  Even with the $9.95 for shipping it would have been cheaper at Inkjet Superstore...  I ended up paying more for the four cartridges than I paid for the printer itself...  What a rip-off !!!
Look for the bulk packs cheaper still!
This is why I use laser
thanks I will check my model and see what kind of savings I get
Thanks for sharing this.  I have a Canon i960 that I use and ordered 14 cartridges at just over $50 including shipping.  Staples sells these cartridges for around $15 each so I am way ahead.
